                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1258.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to France</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram January 26.</p>
                <p>You may join your British and German colleagues in asking French Foreign Office
                    to agree to internationalization of the Chinese reorganization loan which the
                    Department understands was promised at the Paris conference in June last.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
